== Events == * {{ill|Keikō Tennō|ja|景行天皇}} 40th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|110|ja|110}} {{ill|November 1|ja|11月1日}} ） – {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル}} が東夷討伐に出発 * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 2nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1855|ja|1855}} {{ill|November 11|ja|11月11日}} ） – The {{ill|Ansei Edo Earthquake|ja|安政江戸Earthquake}} struck, causing heavy damage primarily in downtown areas with over 7,000 fatalities. * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治}} 3rd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1870|ja|1870}} {{ill|October 26|ja|10月26日}} ） – The Meiji government established a policy that the army adopt French methods and the navy British methods.
== Births == * {{ill|Hōreki|ja|Hōreki}} 8th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1758|ja|1758}} {{ill|November 2|ja|11月2日}} ） – {{ill|Ryōkan|ja|良寛}} , a Sōtō Zen monk, poet, and calligrapher († {{ill|1831|ja|1831}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Hōki|ja|宝亀}} 6th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|775|ja|775}} {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日}} ） – {{ill|Kibi Shinbi|ja|吉備真備}} , a sinologist and court official (* {{ill|693|ja|693}} ). * {{ill|Tenbun (era)|ja|天文}} 22nd year（{{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} {{ill|1553|ja|1553}} {{ill|November 7|ja|11月7日}} ） – {{ill|Yamazaki Sōkan|ja|山崎宗鑑}} , a renka master and haiku poet (* {{ill|1465|ja|1465}} ). * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永}} 20th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1643|ja|1643}} {{ill|November 13|ja|11月13日}} ） – {{ill|Tenkai|ja|天海}} , a Tendai monk (* {{ill|1536|ja|1536}} ). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保}} 6th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1835|ja|1835}} {{ill|November 21|ja|11月21日}} ） – {{ill|Kawaoka Seishū|ja|華岡青洲}} , a physician and pioneer of anesthesia (* {{ill|1760|ja|1760}} ). * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 2nd year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1855|ja|1855}} {{ill|November 11|ja|11月11日}} ） – {{ill|Fujita Tōko|ja|藤田東湖}} , a Confucian scholar (* {{ill|1806|ja|1806}} ).
